       <section>
           <title>Using the Absolute Layout Container - Create PDF Action </title>
           
           <steps>
                <step>
                   <description>Create a background image, like that the 1040 used in the video, or use this one:</description>
                   <figure><link>images/background.png</link></figure>
               </step>
               
               <step>
                   <description>In the UX Builder on the UX Controls page open the 'Data Controls' menu. 
                       Click on the [TextBox Option] give the textbox the name and label of 'Firstname'
                   </description>
                   <figure><link>images/alc2.png</link></figure>
               </step>
               <step>
                   <description>Add a second textbox to the control. Set this textbox's name and label toread 'Lastname'.</description>
                   <figure><link>images/alc2.png</link></figure>
               </step>
               <step>
                   <description>Add a third textbox control to the component that has the name and label of 'City'</description>
                   <figure><link>images/alc2.png</link></figure>
               </step>
              
               <step>
                   <description>Highlight all of the textbox controls in the control tree. 
                       Open the Containers menu and click on the [Container] option.</description>
                   <figure><link>images/alc2.png</link></figure>
               </step>
               <step>
                   <description>From the Container Type list select the 'AbsoluteLayout' option and click OK</description>
                   <figure><link>images/alc2.png</link></figure>
               </step>
               <step>
                   <description>Highlight the Absolute Layout container in the control tree.</description>
                   <figure><link>images/alc2.png</link></figure>
               </step>
               <step>
                   <description>In the properties list check the 'Has background image' property in the Container Begin Properties section.</description>
                   <figure><link>images/alc2.png</link></figure>
               </step>
                  <step>
                   <description>Click the [...] button next to the 'Background image' property.</description>
                   <figure><link>images/alc2.png</link></figure>
               </step>
                   <step>
                   <description>Add the image you want to use. You can also check the 'URL for external Image' 
                       radio button and add the following Image URL:
